<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-28 05:18:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Jennifer Jason Leigh  

</P>
<P>
	 *Image:* If you're looking for twisted and tormented, Jennifer  
Jason Leigh is your actress. 
</P>
<P>
	``Most of the characters I've played are very extroverted or out  
there or living on the edge,'' Leigh says. ``I don't live that way 
at all. But I care about them for some reason, or I want to explore 
that, or I want to be that for a little while.'' 
</P>
<P>
	For Robert Altman's ``Kansas City,'' she ruined her hair and  
wore a set of badly yellowed and broken false teeth. She played 
Blondie, a small-time gangster's wife who idolizes Jean Harlow, the 
glamorous movie star of the 1930s. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought, if this girl's pretty, it's just not going to  
work,'' she explains. ``I wanted her to be something pathetic. It's 
what made me care about her.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Jennifer Lee Morrow was born on Feb. 5, 1962,  
in Los Angeles. Her father was actor Vic Morrow, who died in a 1982 
helicopter crash while filming ``Twilight Zone: The Movie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She made her first film appearance at 9. As a teen, she took the  
name Jennifer Jason Leigh, borrowing the middle part from family 
friend Jason Robards. 
</P>
<P>
	Just weeks before high school graduation, she dropped out of  
school and took a part in a low-budget horror flick, ``Eyes of a 
Stranger.'' In 1982, she starred in Amy Heckerling's brashly 
entertaining ``Fast Times at Ridgemont High.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Since then, Leigh has sought to play psychologically troubled  
characters, usually ones with a streak of dark self-destruction. 
Her roles include a panorama of prostitutes, psychos, phone-sex 
suppliers and junkies in films like ``Miami Blues,'' ``Single White 
Female'' and ``Short Cuts.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Upcoming:* Leigh will star in ``eXistenZ'' with Willem Dafoe.  

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for Jan. 31-Feb. 6:  
</P>
<P>
	Jan. 31: Actress Suzanne Pleshette is 62. Actress Jessica Walter  
is 55. Singer Phil Collins is 48. Singer Johnny Rotten is 43. Actor 
Anthony LaPaglia (``Murder One'') is 40. Actress Kelly Lynch is 40. 
Musician Al Jaworski of Jesus Jones is 33. Actress Minnie Driver is 
28. Actress Portia de Rossi (``Ally McBeal'') is 26. 
