<HEADLINE> 1998 Super Bowl Ads Quiz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Super Bowl advertisers try their best to create unique and  
memorable messages for the big game. Can you recall who was behind 
these ads last year? The answers follow. 
</P>
<P>
	1. This company ran a color TV test pattern in place of its  
Super Bowl ad, saying an ad agency used the wrong courier in 
shipping the real one to the network. 
</P>
<P>
	2. Two bored soldiers on duty at a missile silo shrug off  
last-second concerns that an order to launch an attack may be a 
bogus message from a computer hacker. They send bombs flying toward 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	3. A jealous creature who wanted to be in this advertiser's  
commercials tries to the electrocute his longtime rivals. 
</P>
<P>
	4. Jurors sequestered at this hotel delay delivering their  
verdict so they can stay another night. 
</P>
<P>
	5. Dick Clark rejected pleas from these characters to host their  
millennium bash. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonus: Some big name athletes shed their clothes for a carefully  
edited ad for apparel from this advertiser. 
</P>
<P>
	------	 
</P>
<P>
	Answers: 1. Federal Express. 2. Network Associates. 3.  
Budweiser. 4. Holiday Inn. 5. M&AMP;Ms. Bonus: Nike Inc. 

</P>
