<HEADLINE> Man Arrested in Viagra Theft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CROWN POINT, Ind. (AP) -- A man was charged Thursday with  
stealing 3,500 tablets of the impotence drug Viagra from the 
self-storage facility where he worked. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Steven Drisner, 21, was arrested at the Merrillville police  
station after confessing to twice using master keys to two storage 
units leased by Viagra maker Pfizer Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Lake County Detective Tim Wardrip said none of the pills, which  
were valued at about $35,000, have been recovered. He said Drisner 
was cooperating with police. 
</P>
<P>
	Pfizer sales representatives rented two storage lockers at the  
U-Haul self-storage facility in November. One representative 
noticed 1,600 of the pills missing from a locker on Dec. 17. 
</P>
<P>
	A second sales representative found an additional 1,900 pills  
missing Dec. 29. The pills retail for $10 each, Wardrip said. 
</P>
<P>
	Drisner, who had worked at the storage center for about a year,  
was being held Thursday at the Lake County Jail in Crown Point on 
two counts of felony theft. He faces up to six years in prison if 
convicted and is scheduled for a bond hearing Friday. 

</P>
</TEXT>
