<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Monthly Jobless Rate Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's unemployment rate stood at 4.3 percent in  
December, falling from the postwar high of 4.4 percent the previous 
month, the government said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	But the jobless rate for all of 1998 averaged 4.1 percent -- the  
highest since records began being kept in the present form in 1953, 
the Management and Coordination Agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	The number of jobless in December also fell, totaling 2.73  
million, down from 2.91 million in November, the agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	The number of jobholders shrank by 650,000 in December from a  
year ago to 64.43 million, marking the 11th straight month of 
year-on-year declines. Jobholders in November totaled 64.81 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	The jobless rate for men dropped 0.1 percentage point to 4.4  
percent from November, while the rate for women decreased 0.2 
percentage point to 4.2 percent, the agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	An agency official told reporters that a decline in the number  
of people looking for work in December helped pull down the jobless 
rate, compared to the previous month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
