<HEADLINE> 1957 Titanic Film Storyboards Sold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Fifty-one of the original storyboards from the  
1957 film about the sinking of the Titanic, ``A Night to 
Remember,'' were sold at an auction Wednesday for $2,400. 
</P>
<P>
	The seller, 81-year-old Robert Bell, drew the pen and ink  
sketches for the picture, made at Pinewood Studios in southern 
England, as his first job in the film industry. The buyer asked to 
remain anonymous. 
</P>
<P>
	Phillips auctioneers said the 51 storyboards used to calculate  
the dramatic shots and special effects leading to the sinking of 
the luxury liner sold for three times the minimum price. 
</P>
<P>
	The Titanic sank after hitting an iceberg on its maiden voyage  
in 1912 from Southampton, England, to New York. More than 1,500 of 
the 2,224 people on board died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
