	Jerry West, the Lakers executive vice president, said Wednesday  
a deal with the 20-year-old Bryant was ``imminent,'' the Los 
Angeles Times reported. Bryant's three-year rookie contract was due 
to expire at the end of the 1999 season. 
</P>
