will start with the 1999-2000 season, is believed to be worth close 
to the maximum Bryant can earn under the new collective bargaining 
agreement -- a salary of $9 million and a maximum $1.1 million 
increase each season thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
	Bryant's contract would top out at $14.6 million in the 2004-05  
season. 
