<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Car Sails Off Overpass, Four Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Four of five people in a Pontiac  
Trans-Am were killed Thursday when their car sailed off a freeway 
overpass and crashed onto the highway below. 
</P>
<P>
	The car soared off the roadway at 2 a.m., traveled about 150  
feet and landed on the northbound lanes of Interstate 5 north of 
downtown, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	All five were ejected from the vehicle.  
</P>
<P>
	Police were not immediately able to determine who was driving.  
</P>
<P>
	Two women and a man died at the scene, and a second man died  
later at University Medical Center, said police spokeswoman Michele 
Quattrin. 
</P>
<P>
	A fifth victim remained in critical condition Thursday, she  
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
