<HEADLINE> Ferguson Is Golota's New Opponent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOTOWA, N.J. (AP) -- Jimmy Thunder tore his left Achilles tendon  
and will be replaced by Jesse Ferguson in a 10-round heavyweight 
fight against Andrew Golota on Saturday in the Convention Center at 
Atlantic City, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
	Thunder's injury and his replacement by the 41-year-old Ferguson  
was announced Thursday by promoter Dino Duva. 
</P>
<P>
	The Ferguson-Golota fight will be part of an HBO-televised  
doubleheader with a 12-round match between Michael Grant and Ahmad 
Abdin for the vacant NABF heavyweight title. The telecast will 
begin at 10:30 p.m. EST. 
</P>
<P>
	Ferguson (26-17, 16 knockouts) was knocked out in the second  
round by Riddick Bowe in a bid for the WBA title in 1993. In his 
last fight, Ferguson, who will be 42 March 20, scored a 10-round 
decision over Obed Sullivan last Dec. 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
