<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Student Protests Ban on Goatees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASHTABULA, Ohio (AP) -- A student fighting his high school's ban  
on goatees has asked the help of a bearded congressman, who says 
he's prepared to extol such bearded notables as Abraham Lincoln, 
James Garfield and Santa Claus. 
</P>
<P>
	Rep. Steven LaTourette, R-Ohio, said he was unwilling to take  
Edgewood High School student Byron Gunter's side in the dispute at 
a school board meeting in February, but said: ``I think it can be a 
wonderful civics lesson to see if Byron can follow the procedures 
and change a policy that he doesn't think is right.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gunter became upset when school officials ordered him to shave  
off the chin stubble he grew over Christmas break or face 
after-school detention. 
</P>
<P>
	The school allows only mustaches.  
</P>
<P>
	Gunter countered with a note signed by his mother, indicating  
she gave him permission to grow the goatee. He eventually shaved to 
avoid detention and e-mailed LaTourette for advice on challenging 
the policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
