<HEADLINE> Bernie Kukar To Referee Super Bowl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Bernie Kukar, a 15-year veteran, will referee his  
first Super Bowl on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kukar will head a seven-man crew with 96 combined years of  
experience for the game between the Atlanta Falcons and Denver 
Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
	The other officials are umpire Jim Daopoulos, head linesman  
Sanford Rivers, line judge Ron Baynes, field judge Tim Millis, side 
judge Gary Lane and back judge Don Hakes. 
</P>
<P>
	Referee Gerry Austin and umpire Chad Brown will be alternates.  
</P>
<P>
	Baynes, Millis, Lane and Hakes have officiated in previous Super  
Bowls. 
</P>
