<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gov. Ventura Gets Gun License </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- Gov. Jesse Ventura, a former professional  
wrestler and Navy SEAL who has an armed escort, now has a license 
to carry a concealed weapon. 
</P>
<P>
	John Wodele, a spokesman for Ventura, confirmed Wednesday that  
the governor has been granted a gun permit. Asked whether the 
governor would be carrying the gun at the Capitol, Wodele quoted 
Ventura as saying, ``That's my private business.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Under a Minnesota law, permit information -- including an  
applicant's reason for requesting one -- is not public information. 
It also wasn't known which police agency granted Ventura's permit. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight years ago, Ventura was denied a permit by the police in  
suburban Brooklyn Park, where he was mayor. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura supports loosening handgun permit rules for  
non-criminals who complete gun-safety training and skills testing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
