<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Impeachment Polls at a Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some results from polls released Thursday on President Clinton  
and the Senate impeachment trial. Where results don't total 100 
percent, the remainder offered no response: 
</P>
<P>
	--Do you approve or disapprove of the way Bill Clinton is  
handling his job as president? 
</P>
<P>
	Approve, 67 percent; disapprove, 31 percent (CNN/USA  
Today/Gallup). 
</P>
<P>
	--The Senate has voted to continue the Clinton impeachment trial.  
Do you approve or disapprove of that decision? 
</P>
<P>
	Approve, 41 percent; disapprove, 57 percent (CNN/USA  
Today/Gallup). 
</P>
<P>
	--Regardless of what the Senate does, do you think that criminal  
charges should be brought against President Clinton after he leaves 
office, or not? 
</P>
<P>
	Bring criminal charges, 35 percent; do not bring criminal  
charges, 60 percent (Marist Poll). 
</P>
<P>
	--Do you think Bill Clinton will go down in history as a great  
president, a good president, a fair president or as a poor 
president? 
</P>
<P>
	Great, 10 percent; good, 38 percent; fair, 30 percent; poor, 22  
percent (Marist Poll). 
</P>
<P>
	--Do you approve or disapprove of the way each of the following  
is handling the impeachment proceedings against Bill Clinton. 
</P>
<P>
	Republicans in Congress: approve, 33 percent; disapprove, 57  
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Democrats in Congress: approve, 45 percent; disapprove, 45  
percent. (both from CNN/USA Today/Gallup). 
</P>
<P>
	The CNN/USA Today/Gallup poll of 645 adults was taken Wednesday  
and has a margin of error of plus or minus 4 percentage points. The 
Marist Poll of 882 adults, taken by the Marist Institute for Public 
Opinion, was taken Monday and Tuesday and has an error margin of 
plus or minus 3.5 percentage points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
