<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Chemical Earnings Down 60 Pct. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIDLAND, Mich. (AP) -- Dow Chemical Co.'s fourth-quarter earnings  
tumbled 60 percent, hurt by restructuring costs and falling prices 
for chemicals and plastics. But the results came in just above Wall 
Street's expectations. 
</P>
<P>
	The company reported Thursday it earned $144 million, or 65  
cents per share, in the last three months of 1998, down from $357 
million, or $1.55 per share, in the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales dropped 8 percent to $4.44 billion from $4.80 billion.  
</P>
<P>
	In addition to lower prices, costs to cover the closing of its  
magnesium business and other restructuring moves reduced earnings 
by 45 cents per share. Excluding those costs, Dow Chemical's 
earnings of $1.10 per share were slightly ahead of analysts' 
predictions of $1.08 a share. 
</P>
<P>
	Dow Chemical stock closed up $1.06 1/4 at $88.06 1/4 in trading on the  
New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	For all of 1998, Dow Chemical earned $1.30 billion, or $5.76 per  
share, after restructuring costs of about $1 billion. The company 
earned $1.80 billion, or $7.70 per share, in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales fell to $18.44 billion from $20.02 billion.  



</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
