<HEADLINE> Md. Sen. Released From Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Barbara Mikulski, D-Md., was released  
from a Baltimore hospital this morning after she checked in with a 
bad case of the flu, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Mikulski, 62, is expected to return to the Senate ``any  
minute now,'' said spokeswoman Mona Miller. 
</P>
<P>
	``She's feeling better than yesterday,'' Ms. Miller said. ``She  
did get some much-needed rest and fluids and antibiotics.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The senator checked into Mercy Medical Center in Baltimore on  
Tuesday after feeling faint. Doctors diagnosed that Ms. Mikulski's 
flu-like symptoms resulted from an inflamed gall bladder, and she 
will require routine surgery within the next 10 days, according to 
a statement from her office. No surgery date has been scheduled 
yet. 
</P>
