<HEADLINE> 3 Charged With Making Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WAVERLY, Minn. (AP) -- Police said the bad smell coming from the  
fish shack on Waverly Lake had nothing to do with what was being 
caught inside. 
</P>
<P>
	The problem was with what was being made inside.  
</P>
<P>
	Three men, ages 18 to 21, were arrested last week and charged  
with using a fishing shack as a methamphetamine lab. A fourth man 
was charged with felony possession of the illegal stimulant, which 
is made using a stinky concoction of toxic chemicals. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers responded to reports of trash around the ice-fishing  
house on the lake 25 miles west of Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
	Before they even opened the door, investigators could smell the  
chemicals inside. An officer was overcome by fumes and had to be 
treated at a hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
