<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nets' Kittles, Seikaly Out 4 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- The New Jersey Nets will be missing  
two key players -- guard Kerry Kittles and backup center Rony 
Seikaly -- when they open the NBA season next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Kittles, the Nets' shooting guard who averaged 17.2 points per  
game last season, decided to rehabilitate his right knee rather 
than undergo surgery for torn cartilage. Coach John Calapari said 
Wednesday night he expected Kittles to be out about four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	Kittles' injury was detected before Wednesday's exhibition game  
against the New York Knicks, when the guard complained about his 
knee while having an MRI for back spasms. Kittles had arthroscopic 
surgery on the same knee in October. 
</P>
<P>
	Seikaly, who averaged 13.3 points per game last season, has  
ligament damage in his left ankle and he's expected to be lost for 
about a month. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got some holes,'' Calipari said Thursday. ``But let me  
tell you every team is the same way. What's good is we have more 
depth than most.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
