<HEADLINE> Government Projections of Surpluses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Projections by the Congressional Budget Office of annual  
surpluses through 2009. Included are the overall budget surplus and 
its two components: the Social Security trust fund surplus and the 
surplus for the rest of the federal budget. 
</P>
<P>
	Figures for 1998 are actual, while 1999 and beyond are  
projections. A minus sign indicates a deficit. 
</P>
<P>
	--OVERALL BUDGET SURPLUS:   	
</P>
<P>
	1998 $70 billion; 1999 $107 billion; 2000 $131 billion; 2001  
$151 billion; 2002 $209 billion; 2003 $209 billion; 2004 $234 
billion; 2005 $256 billion; 2006 $306 billion; 2007 $333 billion; 
2008 $355 billion; 2009 $381 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	--SOCIAL SECURITY SURPLUS:   	
</P>
<P>
	1998 $99 billion; 1999 $127 billion; 2000 $138 billion; 2001  
$145 billion; 2002 $153 billion; 2003 $161 billion; 2004 $171 
billion; 2005 $183 billion; 2006 $193 billion; 2007 $204 billion; 
2008 $212 billion; 2009 $217 billion. 
</P>
