<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lawsuit Vs. Jimmy Dean Dropped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- A man confronted by a shotgun-toting Jimmy  
Dean after pulling into his driveway to ask directions dropped a 
lawsuit against the sausage king. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Dean and Christopher J. Dallaglio requested Tuesday's  
dismissal of the $125,000 case. A trial last summer ended in a 
deadlocked jury. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a classic frivolous suit which should never have been  
brought to court, and it did so because I am a high-profile 
celebrity,'' Dean said in a statement released by his sausage 
company, Jimmy Dean Foods. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallaglio claimed that Dean, a country crooner, leveled a  
shotgun at him, told him it was loaded and ordered him to get off 
his property during a snowstorm in January 1996. Dean denied 
pointing the gun at Dallaglio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990128.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-28 17:12:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Super Bowl Quotes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Quotes from Super Bowl players and coaches  
Thursday: 
</P>
<P>
	``Shannon looks like a horse. I'll tell you, that's an ugly dude  
... You can't tell me he doesn't look like Mr. Ed.'' -- Falcons 
cornerback Ray Buchanan, firing the first salvo at Broncos tight 
end Shannon Sharpe. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Ray said that? Well, I think he's ugly, but did I ever call  
him that? No. Tell Ray to put the eyeliner, the lipstick and the 
high heels away. I'm not saying he's a cross-dresser; that's just 
what I heard.'' -- Sharpe. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``We don't look at it as being stars. We look at it as having  
good football players who know how to win.'' -- Broncos fullback 
Howard Griffith on the team's image. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's awesome. He plays the game the way you want to  
play the game, and I'm talking about the dirty stuff, too. He's a 
throwback player. I'm sorry if some of the things he does or says 
offends people, but that's football. That's the kind of football I 
grew up watching. They don't help you up, they kick you.'' -- 
Falcons running back Jamal Anderson on Denver linebacker Bill 
Romanowski. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``The silence was deafening. He comes in and I got a nervous  
stomach. You're nervous for him and shaky, and you know what he's 
been through. You look up to him all year. He's the rock the team 
has depended on. To see him so vulnerable like that, I was just 
proud of the way the team rallied around that.'' -- Falcons center 
Robbie Tobeck on coach Dan Reeves' return to the team from heart 
surgery in December. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``There's going to be some struggles later on in life, but those  
are the choices I made. For me, this adversity and these injuries 
and the things that have happened to me have helped mold me into 
the person I am, the husband and the father I am. I wouldn't trade 
that for the world.'' -- Broncos guard Mark Schlereth on the 
injuries he's had, including 17 knee surgeries. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Flying an airplane is pretty easy. Kicking a football can get  
kind of scary sometimes.'' -- Broncos placekicker Jason Elam on his 
hobby and his job. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``This week is so much bigger than me, as far as being a veteran  
player on this squad. This is about all the former players that 
played here in Atlanta, with all the support and all the calls I 
got from a lot of former players who never had an opportunity to 
experience this. This is for the city of Atlanta. They've been 
waiting so long for this.'' -- Falcons linebacker Jessie Tuggle on 
his Super Bowl mission. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``All year long we played against teams who may not have won as  
many ballgames as us. But when we stepped on the field, we knew 
they had the potential to beat us.'' -- Broncos safety Steve Atwater 
on Atlanta being a seven-point underdog. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Was it a falcon?'' -- Broncos coach Mike Shanahan when he was  
told several birds swooped down at him before flying away during 
practice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
