<DOCNO> APW19990128.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-28 17:12:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Super Singers Plan Halftime Gala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- For Scotty Morris, the full realization of playing  
in the Super Bowl halftime show didn't sink in until he and his Big 
Bad Voodoo Daddy mates saw Stevie Wonder and Gloria Estefan. 
</P>
<P>
	``We honestly didn't believe it until we walked up on this  
stage,'' Morris said. ``We thought it was a really cool joke.'' 
</P>
<P>
	No joke. The hot swing band that two years ago was playing  
Hollywood's underground club scene will be performing for a 
worldwide audience of some 800 million on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's been a really long road,'' Morris said. ``We're very  
appreciative. It's something that's just hard to imagine.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Radio City Music Hall, which is producing its sixth Super Bowl  
halftime, is promising a little something for everybody with its 
11-minute show titled ``Soul, Salsa and Swing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``What a great opportunity for me to sing with Stevie,'' said  
Estefan, who will make her second Super Bowl performance. ``It's 
something we've talked about a number of times. Now we finally get 
to do it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Estefan also performed at halftime of the 1992 Super Bowl in  
Minneapolis, joining jazz clarinetist Pete Fountain as the only 
two-time halftime headliners. This one takes on special meaning, 
however, because she'll be performing in her hometown. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's significant because it's in Miami,'' said the versatile  
vocalist, answering questions in both English and Spanish. ``I did 
it in Minneapolis, and it was great. But here there's a lot of 
Latins, and I'm very appreciative of the honor.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wonder has won 15 Grammy awards during a career that has spanned  
four decades since he was discovered at age 11. His 1984 song ``I 
Just Called to Say I Love You'' earned an Academy Award and is 
Motown's all-time top selling single internationally. 
</P>
<P>
	Surprisingly, he wasn't part of last year's Super Bowl halftime  
show in San Diego, a tribute to Motown's 40th anniversary, which 
featured Smokey Robinson, The Temptatiions and Boyz II Men. 
However, he said he didn't feel slighted. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll celebrate anyone's celebration,'' he said. ``I was just  
excited to be at home, chilling and listening to the various 
artists. I was celebrating just knowing they were there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	More than 1,000 performers will share the field with the  
headliners. Producers spent a year planning the $2 million to $3 
million show, which will use theatrical lighting to transform the 
field into a nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
	Ground crews have less than 5 minutes to roll a 32-ton stage  
onto the field in pieces and assemble it again. The extravaganza 
also will feature huge lighted balloon balls and mirrored disco 
balls, performers on stilts, lasers and various pyrotechnics. 
</P>
<P>
	Producers also are promising a couple of surprises. Three years  
ago, a Radio City-produced show featured Diana Ross exiting the Sun 
Devil Stadium field via helicopter. 
</P>
<P>
	``This year, Radio City knew we had to come up with something  
even hotter,'' said Eddie Micone, a Radio City senior vice 
president who is co-producing the show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
