<HEADLINE> NASD Names Market Regulator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- NASD Regulation has named one of its vice  
presidents, Stephen Luparello, senior vice president of market 
regulation. 
</P>
<P>
	Luparello will be responsible for surveillance of trading on the  
electronic Nasdaq Stock Market, which is operated by the National 
Association of Securities Dealers. The market regulation department 
also works against fraud, insider trading and stock manipulation by 
brokerage firms or brokers. 
</P>
<P>
	NASD Regulation, the self-policing arm of the NASD, announced  
the appointment Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The move came a day after the U.S. Securities and Exchange  
Commission announced that its director of market regulation, 
Richard Lindsey, was leaving to join a major Wall Street firm. A 
successor hasn't yet been named. 
</P>
<P>
	Luparello came to NASD Regulation as a vice president in 1996 to  
help develop its regulatory structure. He has been deputy head of 
the market regulation department since 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
