<HEADLINE> Two-Year T-Notes Go at 4 1/2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in  
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level in three months. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield was 4.575 percent, down from 4.690 percent at the last  
auction on Dec. 29. It was the lowest rate since two-year notes 
sold for 4.025 percent on Oct. 28. 
</P>
<P>
	The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 4 1/2 percent with  
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,985.80. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $15 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling  
$31.9 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
