<HEADLINE> Town Celebrates Floyd the Barber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOUNT AIRY, N.C. (AP) -- Floyd the barber cleared out years ago,  
but his shop is going strong. 
</P>
<P>
	Russell Hiatt has toiled over hair tonics and straight razors at  
Floyd's City Barber Shop since 1946 in Andy Griffith's hometown. 
The shop was a model for the one on ``The Andy Griffith Show'' in 
the 1960s. 
</P>
<P>
	``Andy was getting his hair cut here when I started,'' Hiatt  
said. 
</P>
<P>
