systems, aerospace and missile equipment for $7 billion. But a 
rival automotive supplier, Federal-Mogul Corp., said it might raise 
its earlier $6.5 billion bid, which LucasVarity had rejected 
earlier this week. 

</P>
<P>
 *EMC Corp., up 4 3/16 at 106.    	
</P>
<P>
	EMC ``has chewed up the competition in the fast-growing market  
for computer-data storage,'' The Wall Street Journal reported 
Wednesday. On Thursday, Gruntal &AMP; Co. started coverage of the firm 
with a ``buy'' recommendation. 

</P>
<P>
