the business, Service Corp., said its own earnings would be flat 
due to lower death rates. 

</P>
<P>
 *Informix Corp., down 1 7/16 at 11 7/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	The database software company beat Wall Street's fourth-quarter  
earnings estimates by 3 cents a share on stronger-than-expected 
database software growth. But Chief Executive Bob Finocchio 
declined to discuss his expectations on 1999 earnings or revenue 
growth. 

</P>
