<HEADLINE> Coyotes' Tocchet Scores 400th Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Phoenix forward Rick Tocchet scored his  
400th career goal Thursday night against the Philadelphia Flyers, 
his former team. 
</P>
<P>
	Tocchet was pushed in front of the net, but managed to tip Shane  
Doan's pass past John Vanbiesbrouck as he fell to cut 
Philadelphia's lead to 3-2 with 4:09 left in the third period. 
</P>
<P>
	Tocchet, who entered the season 21st on the NHL's active goals  
list, played for Philadelphia from 1984-92 and scored 215 goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
