<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ill Falcons WR Tim Dwight Practices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Tim Dwight, Atlanta's rookie wide  
receiver-kick returner, practiced Thursday despite a stomach virus. 
</P>
<P>
	Dwight made it through the entire 2-hour, 15-minute session.  
</P>
<P>
	``He didn't miss anything,'' coach Dan Reeves said, ``but he  
didn't practice with his usual spirit.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Also participating in the entire workout were defensive end  
Lester Archambeau and fullback-tight end Brian Kozlowski. 
Archambeau is bothered by an ankle injury and Kozlowski has had a 
foot problem. 
</P>
<P>
	``The ankle is still sore. There's no doubt about that,''  
Archambeau said. ``That's the bad thing about these high ankle 
sprains. It takes a long time to heal. But I am able to move around 
pretty well and it's not any more sore today than it was 
yesterday.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Atlanta also piped in crowd music to simulate what Sunday's  
noise level might be at Pro Player Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	``At least we want to have some practice in case there is some  
noise,'' Reeves said. ``You go in anticipating you won't have a 
problem, but I certainly don't want to go in without practicing.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
