<HEADLINE> Merced OKs Expos Minor League Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Outfielder Orlando Merced, who played for  
Minnesota, Boston and the Chicago Cubs last season, agreed Thursday 
to a minor league contract with the Montreal Expos. 
</P>
<P>
	The signing left the Florida Marlins as the only major league  
not to sign one of the 133 players who declared for free agency 
following the World Series. 
</P>
<P>
	Merced, 32, hit a combined .277 (59-for-213) with the Twins and  
Red Sox, and went 3-for-9 in September with the Cubs, including a 
pinch three-run homer against Milwaukee on Sept. 12. 
</P>
<P>
	He has a .281 career average during a career that began with the  
Pittsburgh Pirates. He was traded to Toronto in November 1997. 
</P>
