<HEADLINE> Two Senators Miss Votes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Two senators missed Senate roll call votes in  
President Clinton's impeachment trial on Thursday: Wayne Allard, 
R-Colo., and Barbara Mikulski, D-Md. Allard rushed home to be with 
his ailing father and Mikulski has been ill with an inflamed gall 
bladder. 
</P>
<P>
	Allard said in a statement that he and his wife Joan returned to  
Colorado ``to be with my father, Amos, who is seriously ill.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``At a time like this I felt it was important to be with my  
mother. I will return to Washington, D.C., as soon as possible. In 
the meantime, I will be keeping informed of the impeachment trial 
from Colorado,'' Allard's statement said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mikulski faces surgery within the next 10 days as a result of an  
inflamed gall bladder that was diagnosed earlier this week. 
